Column Comment.0: PALEO SUMMARY IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the paleo summary report thatis captured.
Column Comment.1: ACCESS CONDITION: textual description of the conditions to be met for someone toobtain access to this data.
Column Comment.2: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y or N flag indicating whether this row of data is currentlyeither active/valid (Y) or inactive/invalid (N).
Column Comment.3: ANALYSIS END DATE: Date on which this analysis was completed or ended.
Column Comment.4: ANALYSIS START DATE: the date that this analysis was started.
Column Comment.5: CONFIDENTIAL INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating that this paleo summary (this rowof data and its subordinates) is confidential.
Column Comment.6: CONFIDENTIAL REASON; The reason why a paleontological summary isconfidential, usually either for corporate security or regulatory restrictions.
Column Comment.7: CONFIDENTIALITY RELEASE DATE: The date that this report will no longer beconfidential.
Column Comment.8: CONFIDENTIALITY TERM: the period of time that this paleo summary is to remainconfidential.
Column Comment.9: CONFIDENTIAL TYPE: The type of confidentiality assigned, such as accessible withpermission from a manager, employees only, no access to anyone etc.
Column Comment.10: DIVERSITY COUNT: a count of the number of different species identified.
Column Comment.11: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.12: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.13: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.14: PRESERVATION QUALITY TYPE: the quality of preservation for the samples used.
Column Comment.15: REFERENCE NUMBER: identifying number or code given to the report.
Column Comment.16: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.17: REPORT DATE: The date on the report. In some cases, this may be the same as theANALYSIS_END_DATE but most often the report is written after the analysis iscompleted.
Column Comment.18: REPORT TITLE: The full title given to this report or summary.
Column Comment.19: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.20: TOTAL SAMPLE INTERVAL: The total interval over which samples taken for thisanalysis were taken.
Column Comment.22: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.23: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.24: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.25: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.26: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.27: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.28: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
